Lamina of cervical vertebrae","Transverse foramina","Vertebral canal"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe vertebral artery passes through the \u003Cstrong\u003Etransverse foramina of cervical vertebrae\u003C/strong\u003E. These foramina are openings in the transverse processes of the cervical vertebrae. The vertebral artery enters the transverse foramen at C6 and exits at C2.  These foramina provide a protective passage for the vertebral arteries as they ascend towards the brain.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EIntervertebral foramina\u003C/strong\u003E - These are openings between adjacent vertebrae for spinal nerves, not the vertebral artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EVertebral canal\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the space within the vertebrae that contains the spinal cord\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EForamen magnum\u003C/strong\u003E - This is the large opening in the skull through which the spinal cord passes\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELamina of cervical vertebrae\u003C/strong\u003E - These are parts of the vertebrae that form the vertebral arch, not involved in the passage of the vertebral artery\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The vertebral artery passes through the transverse foramina of the cervical vertebrae.","The transverse foramina are unique to the cervical vertebrae and provide a protective passage for the vertebral arteries.","The vertebral arteries supply blood to the posterior part of the brain."],"references":["Middleditch, A., \u0026 Oliver, J. (2005). Functional anatomy of the spine. Elsevier Health Sciences","Cramer, G. D., \u0026 Darby, S. A. (2013). Clinical anatomy of the spine, spinal cord, and ANS","Bogduk, N. (2016). Functional anatomy of the spine. Handbook of clinical neurology, 136, 675-688","Adigun OO, Reddy V, Varacallo M. Anatomy, Back, Spinal Cord. 2023 Jun 26. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 30725689","Singh, V. (2024). Textbook of Clinical Neuroanatomy-E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93147"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18001"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"93147","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/93147"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-08-07T12:47:05+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-08-07T12:47:29+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"10715"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"111030"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"